This function establishes a connection to a relational database. As a result a connection handle is returned. The parameter $url is the URL of the database and shall be of the form: jdbc:<driver name>:[//<server>[/<database>]] . If the parameters $user and $password are specified, they are used as credentials for connecting to the database. The $options parameter can be used to set connection options, which can either be specified
as children of an <sql:options/> element, e.g.: <sql:options> <sql:autocommit value='true'/> ... </sql:options>
as map, which contains all key/value pairs: map { "autocommit": true(), ... }

